description: Remove mean from the measured roll rate; integrate using trapezoidal rule

description: Remove mean from the measured pitch rate; integrate using trapezoidal rule

description: RMS value of pitch motion of spar
Notes: Roll

description: RMS value of roll motion of spar
Notes: Pitch

description: List angle of spar, measured in the Port–Starboard (East-West) plane

description: Trim angle of spar, measured in the Bow–Stern (North-South) plane

name: Spar Tilt
description: Total magnitude of the spar platform’s tilt from vertical

description: Direction toward which the spar is tilting, relative to true north

name: RMS Deck Acceleration
description: RMS value of acceleration measured on the deck of the platform

name: Spar GPS  Latitude
description: Calculated Latitude using DegMin, DecMin and DecMin2 as measured at GPS
Notes: This one should be at the antenna location

name: Spar GPS  Longitude
description: Calculated Longitude using DegMin, DecMin and DecMin2 as measured at GPS
Notes: This one should be at the antenna location

name: Spar Northings
description: Northings at the GPS antenna location, measured from platform reference position
Notes: This is at center of the platform

name: Spar Eastings
description: Eastings at the GPS antenna location, measured from platform reference position
Notes: This is at center of the platform

name: UTM Spar Northings
description: Vertical distance from equator

name: UTM Spar Eastings
description: Horizontal distance from central meridian of a UTM zone

name: Avg  Spar Northings
description: 15 minute running average of Spar Northings

name: Avg  Spar Eastings
description: 15 minute running average of Spar Eastings

name: Spar Offset
description: horizontal distance between the spar’s current position and its platform position

name: Spar Offset Direction
description: Direction that the spar is offset toward, relative to true north

name: Avg  Spar Offset
description: running average of Spar Offset
Notes: This is probably 20 min running avg

name: Avg Offset Direction
description: running average of Spar Offset Direction
Notes: This is probably 20 min running avg

name: FB East Wind Speed

description: Highest wind speed of all available quality controlled wind speed measurements, taken at correspoding measured elevations only

name: Avg Best True Wind Dir
description: 20 minute running average of Best Wind Dir

name: Avg Best Wind speed
description: 20 minute running average of Best Wind Speed

name: SW Airgap OL
description: Quality controlled distance of the Southwest Airgap sensor to the instantaneous water surface

name: NE Sg Wave  Ht
description: 20 minute running average of NE Airgap measurement
Notes: Four times the standard deviation of the surface elevation obtained from a rolling 20min record of the quality controlled NE Airgap sensor reading

name: NE Wave Period
description: 20 minute running average of wave energy peak period
Notes: Zero crossing period  of the surface elevation obtained from rolling 20min record of the quality controlled NE Airgap sensor reading

name: SW Sg Wave  Ht
description: 20 minute running average of SW Airgap measurement
Notes: Four times the standard deviation of the surface elevation obtained from a rolling 20min record of the quality controlled SW Airgap sensor reading

name: SW Wave Period
description: 20 minute running average of wave energy peak period
Notes: Zero crossing period  obtained from rolling 20min record of the quality controlled SW Airgap sensor reading

name: Best Sg Wave  Ht
description: 20 minute running average of Best Airgap measurement
Notes: Maximum of the significant wave height calculated from all available quality controlled air gap readings

name: Best Wave Period
description: 20 minute running average of best wave energy peak period
Notes: Zero crossing period corresponding to best significant wave height
